ğŸ§ Speech Emotion Recognition using LSTM

This project performs Speech Emotion Recognition (SER) using MFCC features and an LSTM neural network built with TensorFlow/Keras.

The model is trained once, saved to disk, and reused for prediction without retraining.

ğŸš€ Features

Classifies emotions from speech audio (.wav)

MFCC-based feature extraction using Librosa

LSTM neural network

One-hot encoded emotion labels

Model persistence (.h5)

Training skipped if model already exists

Script-based workflow (no Jupyter notebooks)

Windows-friendly setup

