ğŸ“¥ Dataset Preparation

Place all .wav audio files inside:

data/audio/


The emotion label is extracted from the filename
(as used in common speech-emotion datasets)

Example:

03-01-05-02-02-01-12.wav
               â†‘
            emotion label

ğŸ§  Train the Model

Run:

python train.py

Training behavior:

If models/emotion_lstm.h5 does not exist, the model is trained

After training, the model is saved to:

models/emotion_lstm.h5


If the model already exists, training is skipped automatically

ğŸ”® Predict Emotion from Audio

Use the trained model to predict emotion from a .wav file:

python predict.py --audio data/audio/sample.wav

Example Output:
Predicted emotion index: 3
Confidence: 0.74


Note: Emotion index corresponds to the label encoding used during training.

